==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redfin
<hw>Red"fin`</hw> <pr>(-f?n`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A small North American dace (<spn>Minnilus cornutus</spn>, or
<spn>Notropis megalops</spn>). The male, in the breeding season, has
bright red fins. Called also <altname>red dace</altname>, and
<altname>shiner</altname>. Applied also to <spn>Notropis ardens</spn>,
of the Mississippi valley.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redfinch</ent>⟦br⟧
